article.headline: Southern Utah 73, UMKC 63
article.story: CEDAR CITY, Utah (AP) -- Jason Baker scored a career-high 34 points, including going 8-of-11 on 3-point shots, as Southern Utah beat UMKC 73-63 Thursday night. Baker hit 10-of-16 shots for the Thunderbirds (7-12, 3-5 Mid-Continent Conference), who ended a four-game home losing streak. Trailing 35-31 early in the second half, the Thunderbirds went on a 12-3 run to open up a five-point lead. The Kangaroos (9-10, 4-4) tied it at 46, but Southern Utah pulled ahead for good with a 13-3 run. Michael Watson hit 5-of-7 3-pointers in the first half for the Kangaroos, but he was just 1-of-13 from 3-point range in the second. He finished with 27 points, 19 of them coming in the first half. David Palmer and Tim Gainey each added 12 points for the Thunderbirds. DeAngelo Newsom had eight rebounds, and Dallas Rensch added five assists. Brandon Temple had 13 points for the Kangaroos, who shot just 26 percent from the field in the second half.
